<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-05-30T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-05-30T21:00:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/1349: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Warren</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-31T11:00:00+09:00"><hi rend="italic">May 31,
                                        1922—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 31—9:16
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>90. Foreign Office has given me official statement that Government has
                            decided speedily to withdraw Japanese troops from Hankow. Statement says
                            action is based on policy of respecting the integrity and sovereignty of
                            China and is in keeping with resolutions adopted by Washington
                            Conference.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>